<HL>
   Western Union Extends Offer
</HL>
<DATE>
08/22/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C2
</SO>
<CO>
   WU
</CO>
<IN>
BUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, SWAP OFFERS (BBK)
</IN>
<LP>
   UPPER SADDLE RIVER, N.J. -- Western Union Corp. said it
extended to midnight Tuesday from midnight Monday its offer
to exchange common stock for secured notes.
   Under the offer, the company wants to issue new notes and
common shares in exchange for up to $500 million in
outstanding 19 1/4% senior secured notes and $30 million of
16% notes. The company has said it is seeking at least 95% of
the $500 million and 80% of the $30 million as part of its
recapitalization plan.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   As of midnight Monday, $305.2 million of the 19 1/4% notes
and $1.2 million of 16% notes had been tendered, the
telecommunications company said.
</TEXT>
